h3. Issue Summary
When performing a regex search from the Advanced Search the escape characters are duplicated in the HTML encoded URL. But if you remove the duplicated escape characters from the URL the search works as expected.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add a URL link to a page - http://somewhere.com
 # Go to advanced search and perform a regex search with this term: {noformat}/.*http\:\/\/somewhere\.com.*/{noformat}
# No pages are found
# The encoded URL has duplicated the escape characters in the site search query paramater: {noformat}/dosearchsite.action?cql=siteSearch+~+"%2F.*http%5C%5C%3A%5C%5C%2F%5C%5C%2Fsomewhere%5C%5C.com.*%2F"&queryString=%2F.*http%5C%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Fsomewhere%5C.com.*%2F{noformat}
# Which decodes to: {noformat}/dosearchsite.action?cql=siteSearch ~ "/.*http\\:\\/\\/somewhere\\.com.*/"&queryString=/.*http\:\/\/somewhere\.com.*/{noformat}
# If you remove the duplicated / escape characters from the URL the search works as expected: {noformat}%2Fdosearchsite.action%3Fcql%3DsiteSearch+%7E+%22%2F.%2Ahttp%5C%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Fsomewhere%5C.com.%2A%2F%22%26queryString%3D%2F.%2Ahttp%5C%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Fsomewhere%5C.com.%2A%2F{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
The regular expression finds related content as seen when removing the duplicated escape characters.

h3. Actual Results
No content is found.


h3. Workaround
Try a more basic regular expression for looking for links, the following example works: {noformat}/.*somewhere.com.*/{noformat}

h3. Problem

Copy and pasted JSON isn't formatted correctly when inserted into the Code Block Macro. The JSON loses it's formatting and doesn't retain the correct structure once pasted into the block. 
h3. Environment

Confluence 7.7.3 > 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 * Add a code block macro to a page
 * Copy and paste a block of formatted JSON into the macro:
 * 
{code:java}
{
    "glossary": {
        "title": "example glossary",
		"GlossDiv": {
            "title": "S",
			"GlossList": {
                "GlossEntry": {
                    "ID": "SGML",
					"SortAs": "SGML",
					"GlossTerm": "Standard Generalized Markup Language",
					"Acronym": "SGML",
					"Abbrev": "ISO 8879:1986",
					"GlossDef": {
                        "para": "A meta-markup language, used to create markup languages such as DocBook.",
						"GlossSeeAlso": ["GML", "XML"]
                    },
					"GlossSee": "markup"
                }
            }
        }
    }
} {code}

h3. Expected Results

_We expect that the JSON will retain it's formatting, as in the example box above._ 
h3. Actual Results

_Instead the code block strips the white. space from the JSON strips all white space resulting in the something like the following:_
{code:java}
{
"glossary": {
"title": "example glossary",
"GlossDiv": {
"title": "S",
"GlossList": {
"GlossEntry": {
"ID": "SGML",
"SortAs": "SGML",
"GlossTerm": "Standard Generalized Markup Language",
"Acronym": "SGML",
"Abbrev": "ISO 8879:1986",
"GlossDef": {
"para": "A meta-markup language, used to create markup languages such as DocBook.",
"GlossSeeAlso": ["GML", "XML"]
},
"GlossSee": "markup"
}
}
}
}
} {code}
h3. Workaround

_(Add a workaround, if available)_
h3. Notes

h3. Problem Definition

The below exception is thrown in the {{catalina.out}} file:
{noformat}
20-Aug-2020 14:31:26.113 WARNUNG https-jsse-nio2-443-exec-1854 url:/rest/talk/1.0/comments/updates username:S1114394 com.sun.jersey.spi.container.servlet.WebComponent.filterFormParameters A servlet request, to the URI https://confluence.dkb.ag/rest/talk/1.0/comments/updates, contains form parameters in the request body but the request body has been consumed by the servlet or a servlet filter accessing the request parameters. Only resource methods using @FormParam will work as expected. Resource methods consuming the request body by other means will not work as expected.
{noformat}
(i) Note that the URL will vary - this is but one example.

These warning messages should not interfere with the functionality of the application.

h3. Workaround

The message can be suppressed from the logs with the following steps
# Edit {{<confluence-install>/conf/logging.properties}}
*Note*: This is a different file to that found at {{<confluence-install>/confluence/WEB-INF/classes/logging.properties}}. Please ensure you edit the correct file.
# Add the following line
{code}
com.sun.jersey.spi.container.servlet.WebComponent.level = SEVERE
{code}
# Restart Confluence
